milestones.description: Kevin O'Brien has become the top scorer for IRE in ODIs with 2144 runs, going past Porterfield's 2122
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (3) in ODIs for AFG, going past Shapoor's 3
Porterfield has scored 16 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Kevin O'Brien's record
Craig Young has taken the most five-wicket hauls (1) in ODIs for IRE, going past vd Merwe's record
Mohammad Nabi has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (43) for AFG, going past Samiullah Shinwari

stories.title: Ireland survive wobble to win
stories.subTitle: Afghanistan v Ireland, Dubai Triangular Series
stories.summary: Ed Joyce's 51 and a steady 52-run partnership between Andy Balbirnie and Alex Cusack helped Ireland survive a couple of batting wobbles to secure a three-wicket win against Afghanistan in their opening game of the Dubai triangular series
